Basics
Syntax and Structure:

Variables, Data Types, and Constants.
Operators (Arithmetic, Logical, Relational).
Decision-making (if-else, switch).
Loops (for, while, do-while, foreach).
Namespaces and Assemblies:

Role of System namespace.
Creating and using namespaces.
Intermediate Topics
Object-Oriented Programming (OOP):

Classes and Objects.
Access Modifiers (public, private, protected, internal).
Inheritance, Polymorphism, Encapsulation, Abstraction.
Interfaces and Abstract Classes.
Exception Handling:

try-catch-finally.
Custom exceptions.
Collections:

Arrays, Lists, Dictionaries, Queues, Stacks.
LINQ (Language Integrated Query).
Delegates and Events:

Syntax and Use Cases.
Multicast Delegates.
Event Handling.
Advanced Topics
File I/O:

Reading and Writing to Files.
Working with Streams.
Generics:

Generic Classes, Methods, and Collections.
Threading and Asynchronous Programming:

Threads and ThreadPool.
Async and Await.
Memory Management:

Garbage Collection.
IDisposable and using Statements.
.NET Framework Topics
Windows Forms and WPF (if included in your exam).
ASP.NET Basics (if web development is part of the syllabus).
Practice
Solve coding problems using C#.
Practice debugging in Visual Studio.
Work on small projects to apply concepts practically.
